This used to be the old capital of Malta. Later Capital was moved to Valetta. Here most of the touristic things are actually focused in one place called Vilhena Palace. Mdina Gate, St pauls Cathedral etc all are in the same place with walking distance.
Vilhena Palace: You can take a nice horse ride. The driver explains all the things inside the palace
Popeye's Village
This village was created as a film set. This whole village is a touristic spot actually. Its all fake made to look like a village.

Although it was made as a film set now its a tourist attraction some activities. Entry was around 15 euros. I didn‚Äôt go inside just from outside I was able to take wonderful pictures of the village.
Second Island: Comino

The tourist Island of Malta. People go there only for enjoying nature and do some touristic water activities. You will find jetski, water Paragliding, Snorkeling and nice beaches all around the island. Its small enough that you can walk around the island on foot.
from ferry on way to Comino
I could find only touristic ferries to goto the island. But good thing is that the ferry takes you through some nice spots on the way to Comino.
You might be able to find a nice day trip there where you can do cliff jumping and snorkeling. I found one at the hostel Marco Polo. It was quite good price
Some nice spots on Comino: Santa maria bay, Santa Maria Caves,  Crystal Lagoon.
There is no people living there. So make sure you return before 6pm (which probably is the last time for return ferry). If you miss the ferry you will remain in the island alone without any lights.

translations.EN: Third Island: Gozo

This island is quite big comparing to Comino. So you also should take more time to visit this. I did a hopon hop off bus tour which costed around 13 euro (We got a discounted price at ferry station in Cirkewa)
Return ticket to this island and Malta costs around 5 euro.
